    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Handheld computers first developed in the late 1980s and early 1990s, that had a miniature keyboard and handwriting-recognition software. Originally meant to perform simple tasks such as calculation and organizing, they have since become more advanced. Most PDAs now have the ability to act as a mobile phone, surf the Internet, and run more advanced software.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
